verbose_text: In addition, independent observations that (i) ectopic expression of the T3S effector IncA blocks development of C. caviae, (ii) microinjection of neutralizing antibodies specific for the T3S effector CT229 arrest C. trachomatis development, and (iii) inhibition of CopN interferes with C. pneumoniae growth are all consistent with a predominant and direct role of T3S in developmental progression.
evidence: expression of the T3S effector IncA
